content:
Hello all! What's the usual process after a perf test result like this? https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/90408#issuecomment-964798094

I posted a few thoughts as a comment: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/90408#issuecomment-967448819

download the try builds for the commits that are being compared via rustup-install-toolchain-master and then use those to profile the tests locally via https://github.com/rust-lang/rustc-perf/tree/master/collector
Okay, I'll try that! What should I be looking for?

https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/247081-t-compiler.2Fperformance/topic/cachegrind.20perf.20triage/near/255214991

running cachegrind diffs is the go-to method. run the benchmark that regressed the most and see what results it returns. at that point it's interpretation work.
